<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7533> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7533" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 469. Münzer and Gundel both hold that the cognomen Tricostus was probably included in the Capitoline Fasti. There is no trace of it, although the nomenclature of the gens is much in favor of it. See Degrassi, Inscr. It. 13.1.91, 3581" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/234> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #234" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served, presumably under Romilius, against the Aequi (Dion. Hal. 10.49.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/172> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #172" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Assigned the land to the colonists at Antium (Liv. 3.1.6; Dion. Hal. 9.59.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/166> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #166" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.63.1; Diod. 11.70.1; Dion. Hal. 9.56.1; Chr. 354 (Caelimontiano et Prisco); Fast. Hyd. (Caelimontano et Prisco II); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 91, 358f. Numicius campaigned against the Volscians, and Verginius against the Aequi (Liv. 2.63.5-7; Dion. Hal. 9.56.1-6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/165> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #165" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Caeliomontanus was more probably the cognomen in Fast. Cap. than Nomentanus as reported by Dion. Hal. (CIL 1(2), pp. 102-103; Degrassi 91). Diodorus has {Gr} for {Gr}; see RE s. v. \"Minucius\" no. 29." .
